node.text: @laura.lifeinstyle Thank you. 💖
Its never easy. I dont have kids but i work with special needs kids but I do understand that sometimes we gotta give lots of patience and encouragement to support!!

I felt like yesterday was the day I failed as a mother after being with my toddler @ash1eigh_ng 24/7 for 52 days during this #circuitbreaker period. I’ve been scolding her every single day but yesterday, I scolded and screamed and let out a tirade of verbal abuse at her and broke down twice.

Kids being kids, they don’t take all these hard feelings to heart for too long. This picture shows how she patted my hand when I hugged her as we sat on the sofa to watch tv together.

Swipe for more elaboration or view them on my IG stories. Will get to DMs soon.
.
.
.
.
.
#momlife #momlifeunfiltered #toddlermom #badmom #confessionsofamom #mamasgetreal #thisismotherhood #sgparents #sgmummies #momlifebelike #SGunited #stayhome #breakthecircuit #togetherwewillovercome #behomenowSG #stayhomeforSG
@miss_teatime_sg Oh yes. I forgot to mention that I’m no longer soloparenting as in hubz came back from duty but is still working. 😆
@iamjolene if he is working then almost solo parenting too la.. even tho working from home my hubs can hardly help me on weekdays too..

@iamjolene this cb is definitely trying in many ways and to most people... even though I have help, I suffer from the effects of CB via tension with the many people at home who can't go out and thus are acting abit wierd😅 I can't wait for the reopening too!

It is alright to let it all out once in while. As long as you patch back with her. Eachern does the same and changes the topic when confronted. It actually makes sense because they are too young to know how to handle difficult feelings and how to console someone else. Think about it...some adults are not even good at consoling others or saying the right things when others are upset so much less our 2yo. But I feel u.. this cb is not easy for any of us, much less for solo parenting moms who have no help and have to juggle working from home too! Breaking down is normal.. talk to someone. Also luckily very soon pre schools are opening and we are allowed visitors once again. Take care Jolene!😍 sending u love!
@lawannish Thank you. Kids are so forgiving. 💖 As for the last part of your comment... Yet it’s also bitter sweet sadness when the toddler years pass! I’ll miss every stage. 😆

@iamjolene  Jolene being a mom is tough, those toddler years are trying. Especially when you are doing most of it on your own at the moment.  It's good to recognize when we've lost it and make changes for the future.  Children are amazing at forgiving us for our weaknesses and loving us. These toddler years will pass quickly before you know it💕💕💕
@missyqiqi Thank you. Yes I often give her physical excuses like teething, throat, tummy but I think it’s not leh. These few days, her eating is much better. 😊

Hugs babe, starting i also will scream or scold why they dont eat properly. But realised that sometimes it may due to teething, unwell, or just food strike. Hugs and i believe she also wouldnt want to upset you
@orie_wellness I thought it’s detrimental for them to see us so emotional but it seems like the 2nd time round, she really understood and showed empathy! 😊
Aww it’s ok mama we’ve all been there. It’s important for them to see you express your emotions
@shellandthelittlies Thank you. Oh yes I believe they don’t even hold grudges at all. It’s definitely just us feeling guilty. 😆
We all have days like that hun. You’re an amazing mama and honestly they never remember it’s us that feels guilty for ages about it! 😘
@bryan__girls Thank you. I think when she could talk and communicate more, it would get better! 😊
Aww it's okay mama 💕  I've been there a few times myself and just remember to be gentle with yourself 😊 It does get better I promise 💕✨🎇
@lowcountryblonde You will make a good one! 😊
I can’t wait to be a mom one day
@__clar__ Thank you. Sometimes we just feel so lousy but the kids would think we are doing an amazing job. 😊
We all have those rough days where everything feels like a fail. I promise you’re doing an amazing job ♥️
@laura.lifeinstyle Thank you. 💖
We all have our days. Give yourself grace ❤️
Its never easy. I dont have kids but i work with special needs kids but I do understand that sometimes we gotta give lots of patience and encouragement to support!!
